node.text:
We’ve all played Monopoly & know how to win the game.  The person with the most properties & rentals collects the most money & eventually dominates all their competition!⁣
⁣
The problem is it cost a lot of money in real life to afford rentals properties!⁣
⁣
𝘖𝘳 𝘥𝘰𝘦𝘴 𝘪𝘵?⁣
⁣
What if I told you I discovered a way to get sellers to give you their 𝗵𝗼𝘂𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝗳𝗼𝗿 𝗳𝗿𝗲𝗲!!!⁣
⁣
Seriously…. Like literally they just hand them to you and you can rent them out for cash flow and wealth building.⁣
⁣
I put together a special free report that I want to give to you since you follow me here on Instagram.⁣
⁣
DM me the word 𝗖𝗔𝗦𝗛𝗙𝗟𝗢𝗪 and I’ll send you a step-by-step free report plus give you access to a short training video that will show you everything you need to know in order to get free houses.⁣
⁣
I hope it helps,⁣
⁣
Cody Sperber aka The Clever Investor⁣
⁣

node.text:
Meet Lyle (guy on the right in the first pic). My first #realestate mentor.  He taught me many lessons but the biggest one is the understanding that I’m not where I am in life because “I’m so great”… It’s because great people who have paved the path before me have locked arms with me to help me unlock my full #potential and become the person I always knew I could be.⁣
⁣
Remember that the next time you’re starting to have a little success and you feel your ego taking over.⁣
⁣
Smash like if you can see the value in having #mentors in your life!⁣
⁣
#success #realestateinvesting #codysperber #cleverinvestor

node.text:
𝙄𝙩'𝙨 𝙛𝙪𝙣𝙣𝙮 𝙝𝙤𝙬 𝙩𝙝𝙞𝙣𝙜𝙨 𝙬𝙤𝙧𝙠 𝙤𝙪𝙩…⁣
⁣
I remember asking for help...so desperate for a path...yet they all ignored me.⁣
⁣
I remember them pushing back and telling me every reason it won't work out when I told them my plans.⁣
⁣
I remember their bad advice and misguided opinions even when I didn't ask for it.⁣
⁣
I remember the mean underhanded comments they left on my facebook posts.⁣
⁣
I remember being so alone working on my goals day and night.⁣
⁣
I remember the awkwardness I felt going to all those meetings and events trying to build relationships.⁣
⁣
I remember the silence of the phone when people hung up on me.⁣
⁣
I remember the 1000's of "NO'S" I got before I got good enough to earn a "YES".⁣
⁣
I remember being passed over, pushed around, and sidelined by every major player in my local market when I tried to do business with them.⁣
⁣
I also remember the feeling I had when I was cashing my first $40,000 #realestateinvesting profit check…⁣
⁣
then going on to do over 2000 deals…⁣
⁣
becoming a millionaire by 28 & a multi-millionaire by age 30.⁣
⁣
I also remember the feeling I had when I retired my parents and told them that they would never have to stress about #money ever again.⁣
⁣
I also remember watching all their faces the day I pulled up in my brand new all black Mansory Rolls Royce on 24in Forgiato’s.⁣
⁣
& the Lambos & Porsche 911 GT3RS really fucked them up 😈⁣
⁣
I also remember how rewarding it was to build multiple companies and hire over 100 amazing team members.⁣
⁣
I also remember the look on my wifes face when I bought our first mansion and handed her the keys.⁣
⁣
Now I do whatever the fuck I want.⁣
⁣
total⁣
fucking⁣
control 😎⁣
⁣
Many of the same people that hated either asked me for a loan...or a job...or I dominated them and put their asses out of business.⁣
⁣
Yeah...it's funny how things work out...𝗪𝗛𝗘𝗡 𝗬𝗢𝗨 𝗣𝗨𝗧 𝗜𝗡 𝗧𝗛𝗘 𝗪𝗢𝗥𝗞 𝗔𝗡𝗗 𝗕𝗘𝗟𝗜𝗘𝗩𝗘 𝗜𝗡 𝗬𝗢𝗨𝗥𝗦𝗘𝗟𝗙.⁣
⁣
#codysperber

node.text:
We’ve all played Monopoly & know how to win the game.  The person with the most properties & rentals collects the most money & eventually dominates all their competition!⁣
⁣
The problem is it cost a lot of money in real life to afford rentals properties!⁣
⁣
𝘖𝘳 𝘥𝘰𝘦𝘴 𝘪𝘵?⁣
⁣
What if I told you I discovered a way to get sellers to give you their 𝗵𝗼𝘂𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝗳𝗼𝗿 𝗳𝗿𝗲𝗲!!!⁣
⁣
Seriously…. Like literally they just hand them to you and you can rent them out for cash flow and wealth building.⁣
⁣
I put together a special free report that I want to give to you since you follow me here on Instagram.⁣
⁣
DM me the word 𝗖𝗔𝗦𝗛𝗙𝗟𝗢𝗪 and I’ll send you a step-by-step free report plus give you access to a short training video that will show you everything you need to know in order to get free houses.⁣
⁣
I hope it helps,⁣
⁣
Cody Sperber aka The Clever Investor⁣
⁣
#cashflow #realestate #realestateinvestor #investing #creativefinance

node.text:
💥 𝗗𝗿𝗼𝗽 𝗮 𝗰𝗼𝗺𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 if you can relate.⁣
⁣
When I first started as a real estate investor over 17 years ago I over analyzed everything.  I wanted everything to be perfect because I was so scared I was gonna screw something up. So I bought course after course. I planned, took my time, and tried to get everything lined up perfectly.⁣
⁣
Weeks turned to months and I just kept making excuses as to why I wasn't ready to make my first phone call, or go meet my first seller, or write my first offer.⁣
⁣
I was my own worst enemy.  I mistaken movement for achievement!  I felt that because I was working on my business that I was actively working towards my goals but in reality after the first few weeks I was simply stalling and wasting time.⁣
⁣
There will never be a perfect time to get started. My mentor told me that waiting for the perfect time to begin is like wanting to go on a cross-country road trip…you & your best friend are in the car, bags are packed, & you’re both so excited for the adventure that awaits…but you’re just sitting there waiting for every light in the entire country to turn green at the same time before you hit the gas. 𝗜𝘁'𝘀 𝗻𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿 𝗴𝗼𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗼 𝗵𝗮𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗻.⁣
⁣
Once I finally snapped out of over analyzation mode I finally started experiencing breakthroughs and eventually started making money. 𝙏𝙝𝙞𝙨 𝙞𝙨 𝙚𝙭𝙖𝙘𝙩𝙡𝙮 𝙬𝙝𝙖𝙩 𝙄 𝙬𝙖𝙣𝙩 𝙛𝙤𝙧 𝙮𝙤𝙪.⁣
⁣
It's time to STOP overthinking and simply take massive action towards your #goals.  FIRE, READY, AIM.  That's your new motto.⁣
⁣
We cannot afford to wait any longer. Financial freedom is too damn important.  Too many people are relying on you.  𝗥𝗲𝗺𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿...𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝘀𝘂𝗰𝗰𝗲𝘀𝘀 𝗶𝘀 𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝗮𝗻 𝗼𝗽𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻...𝗶𝘁'𝘀 𝗮𝗻 𝗼𝗯𝗹𝗶𝗴𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻!⁣
⁣
Now get out there…hit the damn gas…and get going.⁣
⁣
🚀🚀🚀🚀🚀⁣
⁣
Your friend on IG & FB,⁣
⁣
C.S.

node.text:
Let's get super real for a second...⁣
⁣
🤔 How many people do you know that are self-made multi-millionaires or are super successful in their careers or their sport?  𝗟𝗶𝗸𝗲 𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗹𝗱 𝗰𝗹𝗮𝘀𝘀 𝗲𝘅𝗽𝗲𝗿𝘁𝘀?⁣
⁣
How many of those successful people or multi-millionaires have a reputation of making excuses?⁣
How many sit around talking shit about other people?⁣
How many are negative and complain a lot?⁣
How many waste time procrastinating or hesitating or overanalyzing?⁣
⁣
The point I'm making is 𝗡𝗢𝗧 𝗠𝗔𝗡𝗬.⁣
⁣
People don't typically become successful by hanging around a bunch of losers.  By having bad habits.  By being negative or toxic.  By making excuses or blaming others.⁣
⁣
This isn't rocket science...it's pretty damn simple.⁣
⁣
Look in the mirror and realize that the only roadblock in between where you are now...and where you want to go is your attitude towards life.⁣
⁣
How do you deal with stress?⁣
How do you deal with isolation?⁣
How do you deal with not getting what you want for long periods of time?⁣
How much are you willing to sacrifice?⁣
How much discipline do you have throughout your days?⁣
How much pain can you endure?⁣
How much control are you willing to give up to get what you want?⁣
⁣
Do you look at challenges as "problems" or "gifts"?⁣
⁣
Zig Ziglar once said..."your attitude determines your altitude"...and what this means is no one is going to give you a shot...not your parents...not your friends...not your boss...NO ONE if your attitude sucks.⁣
⁣
Character is made through pain. Through being mentally and physically congruent internally and externally.⁣
⁣
𝗪𝗶𝘀𝗱𝗼𝗺 𝗰𝗮𝗻𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝗯𝗲 𝗮𝘁𝘁𝗮𝗶𝗻𝗲𝗱 𝘄𝗶𝘁𝗵 𝗮 𝗻𝗲𝗴𝗮𝘁𝗶𝘃𝗲 𝗺𝗶𝗻𝗱𝘀𝗲𝘁.  Remember that next time you're wasting time being a little bitch.⁣
⁣
That's all for now...school is dismissed for the day.⁣
⁣
C.S.⁣
⁣
